Name: spinal polio
Definition: A paralytic poliomyelitis that results in destruction located in motor neurons of spinal cord

Name: bulbospinal polio
Definition: A paralytic poliomyelitis that results in destruction located in motor neurons of brainstem or located in motor neurons of spinal cord

Name: myelomeningocele
Definition: A spina bifida characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord through an opening

Name: tethered spinal cord syndrome
Definition: A leprosy that results in early cutaneous lesions which consist of pale macules that are small

Name: vascular myelopathy
Definition: A neurilemmoma that is located_in the 12th cranial nerve.

Name: myelitis
Definition: A spinal cord disease that is characterized by inflammation of the white matter or gray matter of the spinal cord.

Name: syringomyelia
Definition: An ovarian benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glandular epithelial tissue in which cystic accumulations of retained secretions are formed.

Name: neuromyelitis optica
Definition: A central nervous system disease characterized by inflammation of the optic nerve (optic neuritis) and inflammation of the spinal cord (myelitis).

Name: obsolete Trematoda infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection by parasitic worms known as flukes

Name: obsolete nodular lymphoma involving intrathoracic lymph nodes
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection by parasitic worms known as flukes
Synonym: nodular lymphoma of intrathoracic lymph nodes (disorder)

Name: obsolete Hodgkin's lymphoma
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection by parasitic worms known as flukes
